stration%20has%20in%20Intel%20to%20advance%20key%20national%20priorities%20and%20the%20critically%20important%20role%20the%20company%20plays%20in%20expanding%20the%20domestic%20semiconductor%20industry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20Monday%20filing%20to%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%2C%20the%20company%20outlined%20a%20number%20of%20%26quot%3Brisk%20factors%26quot%3B%20related%20to%20the%20US%20government's%20investment%2C%20from%20negative%20impacts%20on%20shareholders%20to%20hindering%20future%20opportunities.%20Companies%20often%20add%20to%20their%20risk%20factors%20to%20fend%20off%20litigation%20%E2%80%94%20these%20sections%20can%20run%20for%20pages%20in%20quarterly%20filings%2C%20addressing%20everything%20from%20cyberattacks%20to%20pandemics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d88279c3-c379-42a5-b032-6d7c2df6e12f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDilutes%20shares%20of%20existing%20stockholders%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20said%20in%20the%20filing%20that%20because%20it%20was%20issuing%20stock%20to%20the%20government%20at%20a%20discount%2C%20it%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fintc-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edilute%20the%20shares%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20existing%20stockholders.%20The%20company%20added%20that%20shares%20could%20be%20diluted%20further%20if%20the%20government%20purchases%20more%20shares%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22615374ea-b0cb-4c72-9cd7-2d49f311515a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EReduces%20the%20voting%20power%20of%20existing%20shareholders%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20said%20the%20deal%20could%20make%20the%20US%20government%20its%20largest%20stockholder%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20would%20reduce%20the%20voting%20rights%20and%20power%20of%20existing%20stockholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20US%20Government's%20interests%20in%20the%20Company%20may%20not%20be%20the%20same%20as%20those%20of%20other%20stockholders%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20filing%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SEC%20filing%20also%20said%20the%20US%20government's%20powers%20could%20%26quot%3Bsubstantially%20limit%26quot%3B%20Intel's%20ability%20to%20pursue%20future%20transactions%20that%20would%20benefit%20shareholders%2C%20including%20by%20deterring%20some%20third%20parties%20from%20engaging%20with%20the%20company.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2212447532-ab9c-4016-86b8-9211bba7f056%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20could%20hurt%20Intel's%20international%20business%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20said%2076%25%20of%20the%20company's%20sales%20came%20from%20outside%20the%20US%20in%20the%202024%20fiscal%20year.%20The%20company's%20non-US%20business%20could%20be%20negatively%20affected%20by%20the%20US%20government's%20status%20as%20a%20major%20stockholder%2C%20which%20could%20also%20subject%20the%20company%20to%20additional%20regulations%20and%20restrictions%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b052d183-e603-4f71-8037-6c36eddfa8a2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECould%20limit%20Intel's%20options%20for%20other%20government%20funding%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20said%20in%20the%20SEC%20filing%20that%20the%20deal%2C%20which%20involves%20converting%20government%20grants%20into%20an%20equity%20stake%20in%20Intel%2C%20could%20limit%20its%20ability%20to%20secure%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-intel-trump-stake-chips-act-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egovernment%20grants%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20also%20said%20it%20has%20other%20existing%20grants%20with%20government%20agencies%20and%20could%20pursue%20more%20in%20the%20future.%20The%20company%20said%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20deal%20could%20put%20those%20at%20risk%2C%20either%20by%20agencies%20being%20unwilling%20to%20provide%20grants%20in%20the%20future%20or%20by%20also%20expecting%20to%20convert%20their%20grants%20into%20equity%20investments.%20Those%20outcomes%20could%20limit%20Intel's%20ability%20to%