EKhapli%20wheat%20(Emmer%20wheat)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20an%20ancient%20grain%20once%20widely%20grown%20in%20India%20but%20nearly%20forgotten%20in%20modern%20agriculture.%20What%20drew%20her%20in%20were%20the%20many%20conversations%20around%20its%20health%20benefits.%20Unlike%20the%20modern%20wheat%20varieties%20commonly%20found%20in%20markets%2C%20Khapli%20was%20said%20to%20be%20richer%20in%20fibre%20and%20nutrients%2C%20easier%20to%20digest%2C%20and%20gentler%20on%20people%20with%20chronic%20illnesses.%20It%20was%20also%20believed%20to%20release%20energy%20slowly%20into%20the%20body%2C%20making%20it%20a%20better%20choice%20for%20those%20who%20struggled%20with%20fluctuating%20blood%20sugar%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Vaishali%2C%20whose%20mother%E2%80%99s%20fragile%20health%20demanded%20food%20that%20was%20nourishing%20yet%20light%20on%20the%20system%2C%20these%20qualities%20felt%20worth%20holding%20on%20to.%20She%20believed%20that%20by%20cultivating%20Khapli%20on%20her%20own%20farm%2C%20she%20could%20provide%20her%20mother%20with%20meals%20that%20were%20not%20only%20wholesome%20but%20also%20tailored%20to%20her%20needs.%20In%202018%2C%20she%20sowed%20her%20first%20batch%20of%20Khapli%20seeds%20%E2%80%94%20not%20as%20a%20business%20decision%2C%20but%20as%20a%20daughter%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20bring%20comfort%20through%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201280px)%20100vw%2C%201280px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FVaishali-in-the-maize-fields-_11zon-1755766056.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vaishali%20Patil%20Khapli%20wheat%20Jalgaon%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FVaishali-in-the-maize-fields-_11zon-1755766056.jpg%201280w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FVaishali-in-the-maize-fields-_11zon-1755766056-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FVaishali-in-the-maize-fields-_11zon-1755766056-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FVaishali-in-the-maize-fields-_11zon-1755766056-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FVaishali-in-the-maize-fields-_11zon-1755766056-150x113.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-489937%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EVaishali%20came%20across%20%3Cstrong%3EKhapli%20wheat%20(Emmer%20wheat)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20an%20ancient%20grain%20once%20widely%20grown%20in%20India%20but%20nearly%20forgotten%20in%20modern%20agriculture.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20her%20mother%20passed%20away%20the%20following%20year%2C%20what%20began%20as%20an%20effort%20to%20care%20for%20one%20person%20slowly%20grew%20into%20something%20much%20bigger.%20Khapli%20became%20both%20her%20anchor%20and%20her%20purpose%2C%20shaping%20a%20farming%20journey%20that%20would%20soon%20inspire%20many%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20two%20acres%20to%20a%20thousand%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202018%2C%20Vaishali%20sourced%2040%20kg%20of%20Khapli%20seeds%20from%20Pune%E2%80%99s%20Agharkar%20Research%20Institute.%20By%20January%202019%2C%20her%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F482907%2Fbengal-farmer-new-papaya-variety-krishna-halder-hooghly%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20harvest%20yielded%2020%20quintals%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20enough%20for%20her%20family%20and%20for%20saving%20seed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecognition%20soon%20followed.%20At%20a%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%20event%20later%20that%20year%2C%20her%20work%20drew%20attention%2C%20sparking%20curiosity%20among%20farmers.%20By%202020%2C%20cultivators%20from%20Jalgaon%2C%20Baram