o%20tree%20during%20monsoon%3B%20Picture%20source%3A%20Asia%20Farming%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E7.%20Keep%20pests%20and%20diseases%20at%20bay%20naturally%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChikoo%20trees%20are%20generally%20hardy%20but%20can%20be%20troubled%20by%20pests%20such%20as%20mealybugs%2C%20aphids%2C%20and%20fruit%20flies.%20Regularly%20inspect%20leaves%20and%20fruit%20for%20signs%20of%20infestation%2C%20look%20for%20sticky%20residue%2C%20curled%20leaves%2C%20or%20small%20insects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F454949%2Fmonsoon-kitchen-garden-guide-grow-your-vegetables-and-herbs-monsoon-season-temperature-soil%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENeem%20oil%20sprays%20work%20well%20as%20a%20natural%20pesticide%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20should%20be%20applied%20early%20in%20the%20morning%20or%20late%20evening.%20For%20fungal%20infections%20like%20powdery%20mildew%20or%20leaf%20spots%2C%20prune%20affected%20branches%20and%20improve%20air%20circulation%20around%20the%20tree.%20Using%20companion%20plants%20like%20marigolds%20nearby%20can%20help%20deter%20pests%20organically.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E8.%20Feed%20your%20chikoo%20tree%20with%20balanced%20nutrition%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFertilise%20your%20chikoo%20tree%20every%20three%20months%20using%20a%20balanced%20NPK%20(nitrogen%2C%20phosphorus%2C%20potassium)%20fertiliser%20with%20equal%20proportions%2C%20such%20as%2010-10-10.%20Nitrogen%20promotes%20healthy%20leaf%20growth%2C%20phosphorus%20supports%20root%20and%20flower%20development%2C%20and%20potassium%20aids%20fruit%20formation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20organic%20gardeners%2C%20apply%20well-rotted%20manure%20or%20vermicompost%20in%20place%20of%20chemical%20fertilisers.%20Apply%20fertiliser%20evenly%20around%20the%20drip%20line%20(the%20area%20beneath%20the%20outer%20branches)%20to%20enc